MusicLandscape.entities

Class TVShow

  • java.lang.Object
    • MusicLandscape.entities.Event
      • MusicLandscape.entities.TVShow

  • public class TVShow
extends Event
    represents the appearance of an artist in (a certain edition of) a TVShow as a specific event. e.g. "Johnny Cash" on "The Tonight Show"
    Version:
    234
    Author:
    TeM, JS
    Programming Problem Category:
    derived entity classes
    Introduced in:
    ExerciseSheet03
    Stage:
    ES04

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      private java.lang.String name
      the name of this TV show The name of a TVShow cannot be empty or composed of whitespace only.
      private int viewers
      the number of viewers of this TVShow must be non-negative 0 means unknown

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      TVShow()
      creates a default TVShow a default TVShow is a default event with an unknown name and an unknown number of viewers.
      TVShow(Event e)
      creates a TV show from an event this constructor performs some kind of promotion such that it takes a generic event and creates a TV show which is a (deep) copy of the original event.
      TVShow(TVShow tvs)
      creates a deep copy of a TVShow

      • TVShow

        public TVShow(Event e)
        creates a TV show from an event this constructor performs some kind of promotion such that it takes a generic event and creates a TV show which is a (deep) copy of the original event. The resulting TV show has unknown name and unknown viewers.
        Parameters:
        e - the event to copy/promote to TV show
        Programming Problem Aspect:
        derived class copy constructor (deep copy)
        Introduced in:
        ExerciseSheet03
